stories.description:
When no document is selected in the Learning tab, the app shows the last viewed document's summary instead of a library-wide overview. Fix: synthesize a holistic summary from all ingested documents. Backend — add LibrarySummaryModel to app/models.py: LibrarySummaryModel(id: str PK, mode: str, content: str, created_at: datetime). No document_id FK — this is library-level aggregate data. Add to db_init create_all_tables(). Extend SummarizationService with stream_library_summary(mode: str, model: str | None) -> AsyncGenerator[str]: (1) Cache-first: fetch latest LibrarySummaryModel for this mode.   If found: stream full content as a single token event + done event with cached=True. (2) On cache miss:   Fetch all SummaryModel rows with mode='executive', group by document_id keeping most recent.   Fetch document titles for those document_ids.   If fewer than 2 documents have executive summaries: yield error event   {"error": "not_enough_summaries", "message": "Ingest at least 2 documents to generate a library overview.", "done": true}.   Build input text: for each doc ordered by title: '## {title}
{executive_summary}

'.   Query Kuzu for entities appearing in 3+ documents:   MATCH (e:Entity) RETURN e.name, count(distinct e.document_id) as n WHERE n >= 3 RETURN e.name ORDER BY n DESC LIMIT 20.   If cross-doc entities found: append '## Shared themes
{entity_names joined by comma}'.   System prompts by mode:     one_sentence: 'Synthesize all documents in one sentence of at most 30 words.'     executive: 'List the 5-7 key themes across all documents as bullet points. Note connections between them.'     detailed: 'Write a structured overview: main themes, key documents, and how they relate to each other.'   Stream LLM response. Collect tokens. Store in LibrarySummaryModel. Yield done event. Add endpoint: POST /summarize/all — body: {mode: str, model: str | null}. Returns SSE stream identical format to POST /summarize/{document_id}. Invalidate cache (delete LibrarySummaryModel for this mode) when a new document is ingested. Frontend — Learning tab: Detect when no document is selected (activeDocumentId is null or the special 'all' sentinel). Show 'Library Overview' as heading (replacing document title). Call POST /summarize/all instead of POST /summarize/{document_id}. Same SSE streaming rendering as per-document summary. Show mode selector (one_sentence / executive / detailed) same as per-document view. Error state: when not_enough_summaries received, show 'Ingest at least 2 documents to get a library overview.' Tests: tests/test_library_summary.py: (a) test_library_summary_synthesizes_multiple_docs: 2 docs with executive summaries → POST /summarize/all returns tokens. (b) test_library_summary_cached_on_second_call: second call returns cached=true in done event. (c) test_library_summary_error_when_fewer_than_2_docs. (d) test_library_summary_cache_invalidated_after_new_ingest.
